                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107027">Clapcote</placeName>.
                             
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> the <surname>Cook</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_107073">Wareng</placeName>’</persName> grants to <orgName key="org_107004">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                        </orgName> in free alms 7 acres of arable land and all his other land in <placeName key="place_107027">C<supplied>lapcote</supplied>
                        </placeName>, lying in ’peecam de W.’ on the North, free of all secular service, ’ego enim et heredes mei eam acquietabimus per officium nostrum in coquina’ ... For this gift made for the souls of <persName>
                           <forename>Brian</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">fitz-Count</surname>
                        </persName>, his lord, and the lady Matilda his wife, he has received from the monks 60/-, and his son half a mark.
